izabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth FitzWilliam was born about 1152, in Ashington, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Henry de Furneaux. She died about 1209, in Ashington, Somerset, England, at the age of 59."},"et":{"about 1152–about 1209":"umbes 1152–umbes 1209","1156–1214":"1156–1214","1181–Male":"1181–Surnud","1152–1209":"1152–1209","about 1181":"umbes 1181","about 1209":"umbes 1209","1214":"1214","1156":"1156","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","about 1152":"umbes 1152","1181":"1181","Ashington, Somerset, England":"Ashington, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1152–about 1209":"noin 1152–noin 1209","1156–1214":"1156–1214","1181–Male":"1181–Kuollut","1152–1209":"1152–1209","about 1181":"noin 1181","about 1209":"noin 1209","1214":"1214","1156":"1156","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","about 1152":"noin 1152","1181":"1181","Ashington, Somerset, England":"Ashington, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"about 1152–about 1209":"environ 1152–environ 1209","1156–1214":"1156–1214","1181–Male":"1181–Décédé","1152–1209":"1152–1209","about 1181":"environ 1181","about 1209":"environ 1209","1214":"1214","1156":"1156","1152":"1152","1209":"1209","about 1152":"environ 1152","1181":"1181","Ashington, Somerset, England":"Ashington, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth FitzWilliam est née environ 1152, à Ashington, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Henry de Furneaux. Elle est décédée environ 1209, à Ashington, Somerset, Angleterre, à l’âge de 59 ans."},"de":{"about 1152–about 1209":"um 1152–um 1209","1156–1214":